This Red Dragonscale IS common but perhaps not from Nagafen.  If you're just attending Nagafen Pickup Raids, you don't get a chance to see the other creaturs as they typically require a guild style raid.  It's no secret that some Guild have, literally, piles of Red Dragon Scales rotting in the Bank due to how common they are (PC isn't one of those just yet, we still need every scale we get <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  Here is a list of things that can drop Red Scales.<br>
<br>
Nagafen: Fairly rare.  7 day spawn and usually instantly killed.<br>
<br>
Talandar: Rare and random Kunark Dragon.  Requires a strong force to kill.  Scales seem common off of him (I think we've gotten a Scale off of him every time except for once when we've killed him).<br>
<br>
Ragefire: Bonus loot after being killed for the Cleric Epic.<br>
<br>
Nortlav the Scalekeeper: ALWAYS drops a Red Dragonscale. Fairly easy raid if you know what you're doing.  A very solid choice for pickingup a Red Scale if you don't want to go the Naggy Pickup Route and you are incapable of doing the others. <p><A Href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6975" Style="text-decoration: none">Quistil Angelwatch</a><br>
